00:15:00.140 --> 00:15:02.770
BEAU LOTTO: [INAUDIBLE], right?

00:15:02.770 --> 00:15:04.300
Which means that
life is actually

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:07.060
really quite simple, right?

00:15:07.060 --> 00:15:08.620
Very fundamental, very basic.

00:15:08.620 --> 00:15:10.900
At any point in time,
your brain is only ever

00:15:10.900 --> 00:15:15.940
making one choice, one
decision at any moment in time,

00:15:15.940 --> 00:15:18.190
which is, do I go
towards something

00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:20.890
or do I go away from
something, right?

00:15:20.890 --> 00:15:23.260
And whether you go
towards or away,

00:15:23.260 --> 00:15:25.570
the perceptions that you
have, the behaviors you make

00:15:25.570 --> 00:15:28.970
are simply a reflex
grounded in your history.

00:15:28.970 --> 00:15:31.390
You have no free will
in what you're doing,

00:15:31.390 --> 00:15:33.756
perceiving right now.

00:15:33.756 --> 00:15:36.130
It's just like when the doctor
hits your patellar tendon,

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:38.260
and your leg goes out, right?

00:15:38.260 --> 00:15:40.780
It is a reflex,
and that reflex is

00:15:40.780 --> 00:15:43.240
grounded based on what
was useful to do perceived

00:15:43.240 --> 00:15:45.316
in the past.

00:15:45.316 --> 00:15:47.630
OK?

00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:50.030
So whether you go
towards or away

00:15:50.030 --> 00:15:52.317
is determined by your
history, your culture history,

00:15:52.317 --> 00:15:53.400
your evolutionary history.

00:15:53.400 --> 00:15:54.800
You have very little
control in the moment

00:15:54.800 --> 00:15:55.924
of what you're going to do.

00:15:59.280 --> 00:16:04.650
So what you perceive, the
history that you perceive

00:16:04.650 --> 00:16:06.370
is not what the thing
turned out to be.

00:16:06.370 --> 00:16:07.230
It's not the data.

00:16:07.230 --> 00:16:09.624
It's simply what you
perceived before.

00:16:09.624 --> 00:16:11.040
So what you perceive
now, what you

00:16:11.040 --> 00:16:13.500
do now is what you did
before, the history

00:16:13.500 --> 00:16:16.480
of your past perceptions, OK?

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:18.330
So I'm going to show
you how powerful this

00:16:18.330 --> 00:16:19.770
is in the context of sound.

00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:22.260
I'm going to get you to hear
something that originally

00:16:22.260 --> 00:16:24.210
doesn't even exist,
and it's going

00:16:24.210 --> 00:16:27.522
to be simply because of your
history of having perceived it.

00:16:27.522 --> 00:16:28.230
So first of all--

00:16:28.230 --> 00:16:29.920
[GIBBERISH MUSIC]

00:16:29.920 --> 00:16:31.336
--there are no
words in this, yes?

00:16:31.336 --> 00:16:32.679
[GIBBERISH MUSIC]

00:16:32.679 --> 00:16:33.720
It's nothing interesting.

00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:36.402
[GIBBERISH MUSIC]

00:16:36.402 --> 00:16:37.764
Do you hear something?

00:16:37.764 --> 00:16:39.112
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:16:39.112 --> 00:16:40.070
BEAU LOTTO: [INAUDIBLE]

00:16:40.070 --> 00:16:41.190
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:16:41.190 --> 00:16:42.315
BEAU LOTTO: Let's find out.

