00:17:03.861 --> 00:17:04.819
Which is actually the--

00:17:04.819 --> 00:17:06.410
[LAUGHTER]

00:17:06.410 --> 00:17:07.130
--right?

00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:08.930
Which is the power and
the beautiful thing

00:17:08.930 --> 00:17:11.660
about the human brain, right?

00:17:11.660 --> 00:17:13.710
We can imagine.

00:17:13.710 --> 00:17:16.190
But the point here is that
you're perceiving something

00:17:16.190 --> 00:17:19.232
based on your history
of perceiving it.

00:17:19.232 --> 00:17:20.190
And what is this sound?

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:21.606
It's simply this
played backwards.

00:17:21.606 --> 00:17:25.670
[MUSIC- QUEEN, "ANOTHER ONE
 BITES THE DUST"]

00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:28.150
Right?

00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:29.480
Right?

00:17:29.480 --> 00:17:33.500
Which means that you're
like this little guy

00:17:33.500 --> 00:17:36.020
in a space of possibility.

00:17:36.020 --> 00:17:38.330
Your brain can
never do big jumps.

00:17:38.330 --> 00:17:39.860
I can't get from
here to the door

00:17:39.860 --> 00:17:42.740
without passing through
the space between, right?

00:17:42.740 --> 00:17:46.610
At any moment in time, you're
going to make a choice,

00:17:46.610 --> 00:17:50.150
and your choice is to go to
the next most likely possible

00:17:50.150 --> 00:17:52.230
based on your history
of experience.

00:17:52.230 --> 00:17:54.260
And we could represent
this mathematically

00:17:54.260 --> 00:17:57.560
in terms of a space of
possibility, a search space.

00:17:57.560 --> 00:17:59.810
And you can't just teleport
yourself around the space.

00:17:59.810 --> 00:18:02.690
You can only ever
make small steps.

00:18:02.690 --> 00:18:05.620
And you're going to make
small steps determined

00:18:05.620 --> 00:18:08.600
by the dimensionality, the
structure of the space.

00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:12.620
So you're going to the
next most likely possible.

00:18:12.620 --> 00:18:14.990
And what determines the
structure of the space

00:18:14.990 --> 00:18:16.880
are your assumptions.

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:18.800
That's what
experience gives you.

00:18:18.800 --> 00:18:21.624
It gives you your
assumptions and biases.

00:18:21.624 --> 00:18:23.040
Which means that
everything you do

00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:24.270
is grounded in
those assumptions.

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:26.228
It's not that sometimes
you have an assumption.

00:18:26.228 --> 00:18:29.610
You always have an assumption.

00:18:29.610 --> 00:18:31.020
So it's as if your
brain is given

00:18:31.020 --> 00:18:34.950
this data, this completely
meaningless, arbitrary data,

00:18:34.950 --> 00:18:37.680
which is just energy
from the world,

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:40.530
and it constructs
these perceptions,

00:18:40.530 --> 00:18:43.737
and it projects them
out into the world.

00:18:43.737 --> 00:18:46.320
So if a tree falls in the world
and no one's there to hear it,

00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:47.195
does it make a sound?

00:18:47.195 --> 00:18:48.390
The answer is no.

00:18:48.390 --> 00:18:51.750
It creates energy, but
it doesn't make a sound,

00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:53.910
because the sound is a
construct of your brain.

00:18:53.910 --> 00:18:56.640
In the same way that
this screen is not blue,

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:59.310
these chairs are
not white, right?

00:18:59.310 --> 00:19:01.560
That is not red, your shirt.

00:19:01.560 --> 00:19:02.840
It couldn't be closer to you.

00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:06.740
It's actually literally inside
your head, projected outward.

00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:08.580
We color objects.

00:19:08.580 --> 00:19:10.170
We color the world.

00:19:10.170 --> 00:19:11.970
We are the source of
those perceptions.

00:19:11.970 --> 00:19:13.260
We color the world.

00:19:13.260 --> 00:19:17.350
Color is not a function
of the world itself.

00:19:17.350 --> 00:19:21.835
And we project these meanings
even into more complex ideas.

00:19:21.835 --> 00:19:22.710
So here's an example.

00:19:22.710 --> 00:19:25.610
This was a video
made in the 19--

00:19:25.610 --> 00:19:27.060
mid-1940s.

00:19:27.060 --> 00:19:29.460
And of course, there's nothing
meaningful about these two

00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:32.370
triangles in this circle
until we put them in motion.

00:19:35.250 --> 00:19:38.280
And immediately, we start
projecting a meaning

00:19:38.280 --> 00:19:42.400
onto these completely
arbitrary objects.

00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:47.320
We start hating one,
fearful for another.

00:19:47.320 --> 00:19:51.400
This is basically a
horror film, right?

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:54.160
Watch.

00:19:54.160 --> 00:19:54.897
Look at that.

00:19:58.240 --> 00:19:59.680
You're scared for the circle.

00:19:59.680 --> 00:20:01.129
[LAUGHTER]

00:20:09.350 --> 00:20:10.380
Right?

00:20:10.380 --> 00:20:14.010
The meanings don't
exist on the screen.

00:20:14.010 --> 00:20:15.400
Pain is a perfect example.

00:20:15.400 --> 00:20:17.640
There's nothing
painful in the world.

00:20:17.640 --> 00:20:20.490
Painful pain is a
useful perception

00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:25.440
about the world that exists
inside your head, right?

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:28.440
And so what's true for color,
what's true for objects,

00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:31.500
is actually true
for other people.

00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:34.630
You have no access to the
spectral qualities of surfaces,

00:20:34.630 --> 00:20:38.820
but nor do you have access
to inside someone's head.

00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:42.150
You have no access to
another person's thoughts.

00:20:42.150 --> 00:20:46.070
People are just the sources
of meaningless data, right?

00:20:46.070 --> 00:20:48.920
You are the source of
your own meaningless data.

00:20:48.920 --> 00:20:51.350
You then project a
meaning onto them.

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:54.530
Every personality you
perceive is actually inside

00:20:54.530 --> 00:20:57.790
you projected outward.

00:20:57.790 --> 00:21:00.160
You have no way of
determining whether or not

00:21:00.160 --> 00:21:01.786
your perceptions are
actually accurate.

00:21:01.786 --> 00:21:03.243
When you connect
with someone, it's

00:21:03.243 --> 00:21:05.154
because your perceived
meaning of them

00:21:05.154 --> 00:21:06.820
happens to coincide
with their perceived

00:21:06.820 --> 00:21:09.360
meaning of themselves.

00:21:09.360 --> 00:21:10.230
Right?

00:21:10.230 --> 00:21:12.930
We color other people.

00:21:12.930 --> 00:21:14.415
You're a complete group within.

00:21:14.415 --> 00:21:16.540
So I'm going to show you
how powerful this is, just

00:21:16.540 --> 00:21:19.660
simply in terms of a
funny American football

00:21:19.660 --> 00:21:23.590
situation where, notice how
the behavior of the quarterback

00:21:23.590 --> 00:21:27.790
completely changes his perceived
meaning by the defense.

00:21:27.790 --> 00:21:28.455
OK?

