00:51:51.730 --> 00:51:54.280
And what's more, the most
successful systems in nature

00:51:54.280 --> 00:51:59.824
are also the ones that
play into adulthood, right?

00:51:59.824 --> 00:52:01.240
So the point is,
you have to adopt

00:52:01.240 --> 00:52:04.720
this way of being
if you're going

00:52:04.720 --> 00:52:05.980
to ever explore the world.

00:52:05.980 --> 00:52:08.590
Otherwise, you'll be
stuck in your own biases

00:52:08.590 --> 00:52:10.090
and your own
assumptions, and you'll

00:52:10.090 --> 00:52:14.080
continue to live with the
idea that Barack Obama was

00:52:14.080 --> 00:52:17.678
born in Africa, and not
from the States, right?

00:52:21.150 --> 00:52:24.180
So the third point
is that in order

00:52:24.180 --> 00:52:26.670
to be able to ask these
questions, to be in a lab,

00:52:26.670 --> 00:52:29.730
for instance, where
questions are a good thing,

00:52:29.730 --> 00:52:31.170
you need an ecology.

00:52:31.170 --> 00:52:33.630
It's not good enough just to
be on your own, necessarily.

00:52:33.630 --> 00:52:36.690
You need an environment where
asking questions, being playful

00:52:36.690 --> 00:52:38.760
is actually a
positive thing, right?

00:52:38.760 --> 00:52:41.244
Hence the power of
the host, the leader.

00:52:41.244 --> 00:52:43.410
And if you ask people, what
defines good leadership,

00:52:43.410 --> 00:52:45.207
you get all kinds
of answers, right?

00:52:45.207 --> 00:52:47.040
But there are only three
that are associated

00:52:47.040 --> 00:52:48.690
with the success
of any one company,

00:52:48.690 --> 00:52:52.770
which has lead by example, admit
mistakes, and see qualities

00:52:52.770 --> 00:52:54.060
in others.

00:52:54.060 --> 00:52:56.740
These are the three that define
the success of any one company.

00:52:56.740 --> 00:52:58.365
And the reason is
because they actually

00:52:58.365 --> 00:53:00.207
create an environment of play.

00:53:00.207 --> 00:53:02.540
The first one, lead by example,
is space that is secure.

00:53:02.540 --> 00:53:05.664
You can't ask questions
and play outside of space

00:53:05.664 --> 00:53:06.330
that is trusted.

00:53:06.330 --> 00:53:09.240
This is very well known.

00:53:09.240 --> 00:53:10.710
The second is admit mistakes.

00:53:10.710 --> 00:53:13.043
That is space that celebrates
uncertainty, that mistakes

00:53:13.043 --> 00:53:15.060
are OK, questions are OK.

00:53:15.060 --> 00:53:16.175
Not answers.

00:53:16.175 --> 00:53:17.500
All right?

00:53:17.500 --> 00:53:20.010
Not to say that answers
are not important,

00:53:20.010 --> 00:53:22.052
but you have to have
a good question first.

00:53:22.052 --> 00:53:23.760
And the third is see
qualities in others.

00:53:23.760 --> 00:53:26.010
That's the space that
celebrates diversity.

00:53:26.010 --> 00:53:27.510
Again, three of
the parameters are

00:53:27.510 --> 00:53:31.340
essential for a quality of play.

00:53:31.340 --> 00:53:35.170
So we'll finish with two
examples of leadership.

